07/12/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Prosecutors in Albania will continue to prioritise cases involving organised crime and corruption, a commitment that was confirmed by chief prosecutor Ina Rama on Monday (December 6th). Rama is convinced that institutions will prevail by co-operating domestically and internationally. She was meeting with Belgian Federal Johan Delmulle in Tirana, where co-operation between institutions was also discussed. Delmulle emphasised the importance of implementing a law on money laundering law. (Ora News, Telegrafi, News 24 - 06/12/10)
